author: National Geographic
description:
With 90 percent of its habitat lost and threats from a myriad of predators, the Florida grasshopper sparrow faces overwhelming odds. But these little birds are resilient. 

Watch The Little Brown Bird now on Nat Geo's YouTube channel and discover more about the efforts to save this species and their home: https://on.natgeo.com/44EfEso
title: The resilience of Florida grasshopper sparrows | The Little Brown Bird

author: National Geographic
description:
As a colony of Gentoo penguins hesitate on a rock cliff, a 700-pound Leopard Seal, the "Grizzly Bear of the sea," lies in wait for its next meal. But the penguins have a survival strategy to outsmart the deadly killer. Still, not everyone will survive the chaotic dive as each penguin races to escape. Who will survive? 

Secrets of the Penguins is now streaming on @disneyplus and @hulu  https://on.natgeo.com/4cHzyFv

author: National Geographic
description:
Jo Franco hits the streets of São Paulo, Brazil, to discover Italian culture in a country that boasts 6 million residents of Italian heritage. Her mission: find out why Italian and Brazilian culture has meshed so well, and sample as much food as possible. Spoiler alert: lots of meat and cheese in this episode.
